 ARCTRUST Properties, Inc. - Retail Net Lease and Build-to-Suit Developments












 ARCTRUST Properties, Inc. - Retail Net Lease and Build-to-Suit Developments







ARCTRUST Properties

Clifton, NJ
07013

 


Resources



ARCTRUST Properties on PinterestARCTRUST Properties // Wordpress






Social Profiles







 
Specializing in retail net lease and build-to-suit properties, ARCTRUST Properties, Inc., meets the needs of national tenants. Established in 1985, the company has facilitated more than 300 developments totaling over $3 billion in aggregate value. ARCTRUST Properties has extensive experience in all phases of the retail development process including municipal entitlements, leasing, environmental expertise, land closing, and construction. The firm is most active in the metropolitan areas of New York, Philadelphia and Washington, DC. and Florida. 

ARCTRUST Properties’ sponsored ARCTRUST, is guided by Chariman and Founder, Robert J. Ambrosi and President and Chief Operating Officer, James M. Steuterman. Averaging over 35 years of experience each, they bring their expertise in developing, acquiring and managing single tenant net lease properties leased long-term to nationally and regionally recognized credit tenants.












Arc Properties - Partnering with Nationally Known Retailers












Arc Properties - Partnering with Nationally Known Retailers



Biography
ARCTRUST, Inc. is a respected developer of properties for nationwide retail chains with a presence encompassing the New York to Washington DC to Florida corridor as well as metropolitan cities with international airports.  The company focuses on retail net lease properties and build-to-suit projects that are leased long-term to nationally recognized tenants.   The company has earned its reputation as the “Maker of Reliable Net Lease Properties”, with a proven track record in all phases of development including land acquisition, entitlements, budgeting, construction, and project management. For over 30 years, ARCTRUST, Inc. and its affiliates have been a leading provider of commercial real estate. During that time, the company has completed more than 500 transactions with an aggregate value in excess of $3 Billion and has been the recipient of a number of industry awards, including the Phoenix Award, while developing close relationships with nationally recognized tenants, developers, and other industry sources.









